"Long Way 2 Go" is the second single from American pop-R&B singer Cassie's debut album, Cassie (2006).

The video for the single was shot in Los Angeles during the week of August 20, 2006, and its world premiere was on MTV's Total Request Live on September 12, 2006. The video debuted on the show's top ten video countdown on September 14, subsequently peaking at number three. It begins with shots of the ocean near Los Angeles and cuts to Cassie checking her laptop with her dog, a West Highland White Terrier. On the social networking website she visits, she denies "friend requests" from men she believes are unworthy. A video screen opens, and her producer, Ryan Leslie, responds to Cassie's lines in the song: "You're not into it?".

As the chorus begins, Cassie's friends show up at the door and she prepares to go out. This sequence, and the remainder of the video, is intercut with shots of Cassie dancing in front of a large fan and lights. Cassie and her friends walk down the street and, after passing Leslie, enter a nightclub, where Cassie dances with a boy and leaves abruptly. She goes back home to her laptop and dog and goes back to the social networking site and adds the boy she danced with to her friends list. Right before Cassie signs off her laptop, the profile page she is on is that of Erik White, the director of the music video.
